« 2nd hug » will be open on 29th of june at @openinggallery in Tribeca.  @sozitagood 

The exhibition "2nd hug" could be a reflection as much related to life as to art. Offering a second chance as well as a second reading seems a necessary empathetic gesture. This show brings together a set of sculptures made in 2019 for an exhibition. Without exception, all the works were produced with objects gleaned from the streets of NYC.
the sculptures are the reflection of a second acceptance, they seem to be made of intertwining, of fusion, with objects sometimes reduced to their simplest materiality.

All these works have already been exhibited once, thus achieving a second attention, a second look, a second life in a kind of upcycling.

.

The plaster band is undoubtedly the material I used the most during my practice as a sculptor. It allows for faster execution, and it's relative lightness offers comfort to the model.

One view from Andrea @_____________cora, one of my best-performing models

.
In sculpture the demolding is always a particular moment, there is always an emotion and more clearly on the body cast. 
The greatest sensation is always for the model who feels liberated from a shape perfectly adapted to his body. 
The body of the model has the feeling of an animal moult, as if a part of the body detaches, frees. 
A body cast can be dangerous, you should never lock the body in the plaster, so it’s advisable to master the techniques of demoulding as the restraints of undercut. 

@_____________cora #model #sculpture #casting#danielfirmanstudio

.
The moulding of the complete head is probably the most complex to execute. 
Impossible to make with a claustrophobic model. It requires great mastery and the model must have great confidence of the molder. 
The person will be locked totally in the dark with almost no hearing. The mouth is blocked and only the two nostrils allow breathing.
The casting takes about 20 to 30 mins, it’s very long in these conditions. 
Thank you to all my models who accepted this performance🙏🏼♥️

About this fantastic time and memories in Amsterdam with @alexdanielsreflex for my second solo show « Re-enchantment » Thank you Alex 💥
The exhibition will be until February 10, 2024.

« This new Mini-Gathering series offers mini-scenarios for a slapstick comedy, where the situation seems disastrous and bogged down. The sculptures show unweakened bodies, standing and submerged by various objects and materials, in a sort of rot-proof, almost sticky intertwining. But Daniel Firman's sculptural work also opens up positive perspectives, forms of rebirth, new contingencies, as the title re-enchantment indicates. These works are ultimately beautiful to see and the materials which usually inflict so much distress on us suddenly become formal and aesthetic promises »
